		"ITEM_NAME" : "ultraDocumentBody",
		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_b17ed749-88f5-4fd3-8b5d-6a4f01a142aa\"><p>This is your Module 2 Exam for Color Theory Lab<\/p><p>Using the pdf file&nbsp;<strong>\"1967 Mustang\"<\/strong>, create four variations of color harmonies of your choice to add color and life into the image.<\/p><p>Print this out in a 8.5x11 or A4 size water color paper (any, as long as it fits) add amazing colors into it, then paste it in the black side of a 10x15 inch illustration board. Put your group member's names in the back.<\/p><p>You may use poster color, acrylics or marker pens. We'll go old-school, traditional coloring techniques. No digital art.<\/p><p>I've also included some great inspirations from around the web.<\/p><p>Onliners and face-to-face students will do the same thing.<\/p><p>Submission is on the October 20, 21. Depending on where your lab class falls.<\/p><\/div>",
		"ITEM_ADDED_TIME" : "2023-10-05T18:10:47.853Z"
