		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_c9b03237-f5f4-403f-a0c5-27715e2209ff\"><p>For&nbsp;<strong>Week 6<\/strong>, we continued to have an Adobe Photoshop demonstration. However, this time we delved deeper by making use of the tools we discussed the week prior. Such tools were used to&nbsp;<strong>restore<\/strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>edit&nbsp;<\/strong>out imperfections from images. We also tackled how to&nbsp;<strong>add colors<\/strong>&nbsp;on black and white images and as well as basic&nbsp;<strong>color grading&nbsp;<\/strong>using Photoshop.&nbsp;<\/p><p>It is best to learn Adobe Photoshop hands on with a lot of experimentation from your end. That is the reason why I took time to hold these demonstrations. Do not fret, I wont be technical with regard to your knowledge with&nbsp;<em>tone<\/em>,&nbsp;<em>temperature<\/em>,&nbsp;<em>brightness<\/em>,&nbsp;<em>contrast<\/em>,&nbsp;<em>curves<\/em>, and other settings and features. I am more concerned with you learning the \"<strong>how's<\/strong>\" of basic&nbsp;<em>Digital Photography<\/em>.<\/p><br><p>For those that missed the Week 6 sychronous meeting and are still not confident with their software skills just yet, you may watch a recording of my class embedded below.&nbsp;<\/p><br><p><a href=\"https:\/\/youtube.com\/embed\/cTK08kwrCU4\" data-bbtype=\"video\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/youtube.com\/embed\/cTK08kwrCU4&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;WEEK 6 - Using Photoshop Tools and Features&quot;}\">WEEK 6 - Using Photoshop Tools and Features<\/a><\/p><\/div>",
