		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_5d4efa95-2bc6-40cb-8842-4ec97d8b6a92\"><h6><span style=\"font-family: Open Sans;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>Exposure<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/h6><h6>&nbsp;<\/h6><h6><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-19617219_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;Exposure.png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Exposure.png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;Exposure.png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:2372803,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/93\/935126AFC17573A0F47A236E45748D6E\/f090bc4b20de49289a93ab4655a08dcf\/Exposure.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;Exposure.png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:914.1122913505311,&quot;height&quot;:200}\">Exposure.png<\/a>&nbsp;<\/h6><p>This adjustment allows you to control the overall brightness of your image. Increasing the exposure makes the image brighter, while decreasing it makes the image darker. It's a fundamental adjustment that helps correct underexposed or overexposed photos and achieve the desired overall brightness.<\/p><h4>Contrast<\/h4><h6>&nbsp;<\/h6><h6><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-19617333_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;Contrast.png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Contrast.png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;Contrast.png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:3578528,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/93\/935126AFC17573A0F47A236E45748D6E\/aa751942c03f4e1ca3e5bd575dd7ffb3\/Contrast.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;Contrast.png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:914.1122913505311,&quot;height&quot;:200}\">Contrast.png<\/a>&nbsp;<\/h6><p><span style=\"color: #000000\">This adjustment allows you to control the overall brightness of your image. Increasing the exposure makes the image brighter, while decreasing it makes the image darker. It's a fundamental adjustment that helps correct underexposed or overexposed photos and achieve the desired overall brightness.<\/span><\/p><\/div>",
