		"ITEM_NAME" : "M1 Summative Assessment",
		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<!-- {\"bbMLEditorVersion\":1} --><div>\n <p>Dear students,<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>I am writing to inform you of the upcoming M1 Summative Assessment. The details are as follows:<\/p>\n <br>\n <ul>\n  <li style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\n          padding-left: 1.487rem;\"><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>What:<\/strong><\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">The M1 Summative Assessment is a fully-online asynchronous exam that will be available from September 9 to 10, 2023.<\/span><\/li>\n  <li style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\n          padding-left: 1.487rem;\"><span style=\"color: #1c8845\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>When:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">The exam will be open from 12:00 AM on Saturday, September 9 to 11:59 PM on Sunday, September 10.<\/span><\/li>\n  <li style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\n          padding-left: 1.487rem;\"><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>Nature:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">The exam is a 1-hour and 30-minute (90-minute) exam with one attempt only.<\/span><\/li>\n  <li style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\n          padding-left: 1.487rem;\"><span style=\"color: #666666\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>Coverage:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">The exam will cover all topics in M1 except for the logic part of \"Sets and Logic\".<\/span><\/li>\n  <li style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\n          padding-left: 1.487rem;\"><span style=\"color: #a234b5\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>Items:<\/strong><\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">There will be<\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">60 items on the exam.<\/span><\/li>\n <\/ul>\n <br>\n <p>Please note that even though some topics were not discussed directly in the synchronous sessions, they are still part of the coverage. This is because it is expected that you will access and study the content even when we are not meeting synchronously.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>We will still have a synchronous class this week to discuss Sets and Venn Diagrams. This will help you prepare for the exam.<\/p>\n <p>If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me via our Official MS Teams Group.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Thank you,<\/p>\n <p>Sir Neal<\/p>\n<\/div>",
