		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<!-- {\"bbMLEditorVersion\":1} --><div>\n <p>Dear students,<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>I'd like to address a potential hiccup that some of you might be encountering while attempting to tackle FA1.1. It has come to my attention that a few of you might be experiencing&nbsp;<strong>difficulties with the images, with broken thumbnails<\/strong>&nbsp;hindering your progress.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Rest assured, I've taken active steps to troubleshoot this issue. After careful investigation,<strong>&nbsp;I've identified a workaround<\/strong>&nbsp;that seems to be effective for the time being. To potentially resolve this matter, I recommend&nbsp;<strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">accessing Blackboard in Incognito Mode<\/span><\/em><\/strong><strong><em>.&nbsp;<\/em><\/strong>This approach has yielded positive results during my testing.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Additionally, I believe that&nbsp;<strong>certain Chrome extensions might inadvertently interfere with image display<\/strong>. Hence, it's a good practice to disable any extensions that might be causing this obstruction.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>I kindly request each of you to give this approach a try on your end. If you find that this solution works and the images become accessible as intended, I would greatly appreciate it if you could inform me of your success.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Thank you for your patience and cooperation in addressing this matter promptly. Your feedback is invaluable in ensuring a seamless learning experience for everyone.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Best regards,<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Sir Neal Lasta<\/p>\n<\/div>",
