		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_58fe8100-8708-485c-9d54-8c9867bde73a\"><br> \n <p><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17899228_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;istockphoto-180819641-612x612.jpg&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;istockphoto-180819641-612x612.jpg&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;istockphoto-180819641-612x612.jpg&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:18257,&quot;isDecorative&quot;:true,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/jpeg&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inline&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/CD\/CDE06A923AEBBE094F7905D2A7A2B52C\/a2dacd86190f4795a69463f9ee48e0c9\/istockphoto-180819641-612x612.jpg&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;istockphoto-180819641-612x612.jpg&quot;}\">istockphoto-180819641-612x612.jpg<\/a><\/p> \n <br><\/div><a data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_3308a4ce-00bf-40c7-906f-9c9e9a241712\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;UNSAFE_HTML_20211106045820.html&quot;}\" data-bbtype=\"embedded-unsafe-html\" href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17899230_1\"><\/a><div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_825d80ed-13a0-4d4d-a747-f84d8fadf758\"><p><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong><em>Important note:<\/em><\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong><em>Module 2 will be full face to face classes.<\/em><\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong><em>Instead of 12 weeks the new duration per term is 14 weeks.<\/em><\/strong><\/span><\/p><\/div><div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_6290aa55-1c8e-45d7-9bba-1ad8b2269855\"><h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-family: Courier New;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>COURSE GUIDELINES:<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/h4> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Modular System<\/strong><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>Module Grade of INC (Incomplete)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ A student who was not able to submit a course requirement due to medical or emergency reasons will get an<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">incomplete grade of INC.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ Incomplete grade of INC can be completed to any passing mark, from 3.00 to 1.00.<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>Module Grade of IP (In Progress)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ A student who failed a module will get a module grade of IP.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ An IP module grade can only be converted, upon completion, to a grade of 3.00.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ If a student passes at least one module,<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;o He\/she will just need to convert all modules with IP to 3.00, and not repeat the whole&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;course.&nbsp;<\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"> o He\/she will be given an additional term to convert all modules with a grade of IP to 3.00 for free.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"> o A course with an IP in any of the modules by the end of the term will get a course grade of IP for the<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"> course.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"> o A course will remain to have a course grade of IP until the student gets a passing grade in all modules.<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ After an additional term, if the student is not able to convert the IP to 3.00, the student needs to re-enroll the module as a Remedial Module in the following term, if offered, and not the whole course.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>What will be the basis of a Grade of 5.00 (F)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ The student will get a course grade of 5.00&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ In case he\/she violated the Academic Integrity Policy of the School in any of the modules (a module grade<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">of 5.00 will be given) regardless of class standing.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ in case he incurred a 100% absence (module grade of ABS) in any of the modules, regardless of his<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">performance in other modules.<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ if he gets IP in all the modules. Under this situation, the student needs to re-enroll in the course in<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">the following term, if offered.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>Converting Modules that you Fail into Passing Mark<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ If you fail Module 1, you get IP, not 5.00&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ If you fail Module 2, you get IP, not 5.00<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\">‚Ä¢ If you get IP to all modules, you get a course grade of 5.00. That means You need to re-enroll in the course.<\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ If you pass at least one module in a course, you will be given an additional term to convert IP grade<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">into 3.00. You repeat the module not the course.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ If you fail to complete all the modules after one term, you will need to re-enroll modules as remedial<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">modules.<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">‚Ä¢ You need to pass all modules in a prerequisite course before you can enroll in the advanced course.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p><\/div>",
