		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<p>Good day, everyone!<\/p><br><p>Please open your&nbsp;<strong>BLACKBOARD&nbsp;<\/strong>and find&nbsp;<strong>Cover Letter and CV Submission<\/strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Mock Job Interview<\/strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>M2 Final Assessment - Final Job Interview<\/strong>. Please follow the instructions carefully.<\/p><br><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>THE FINAL JOB INTERVIEW (M2 SUMMATIVE ASSESSMENT) IS FACE-TO-FACE.<\/strong><\/span><\/p><br><p>SCHEDULE:&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>OCTOBER 7, 2023<\/strong><\/span><strong>&nbsp;(SATURDAY) @ 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM<\/strong><\/p><br><p>INDIVIDUAL SCHEDULE: *Initially, you are asked to go whenever you are free during the day. However, let's wait for the final instructions.<\/p><br><p>WHERE:&nbsp;<strong>3RD FLOOR<\/strong>&nbsp;(Room 301, 303, 305, 307, 309)<\/p><br><p>WHAT TO BRING:&nbsp;<strong>Cover Letter &amp; Skills-based CV<\/strong><\/p><br><p>WHAT TO WEAR:&nbsp;<strong>FORMAL\/BUSINESS ATTIRE<\/strong><\/p><br><p><em>*Note: I will not be your interviewer. Invited instructors from well-known institutions are tasked to act as real interviewers during the day.<\/em><\/p><br><br><p><strong>REMINDER: MODULE SUMMATIVE ASSESSMENTS ARE 70% OF YOUR GRADE.&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p><p><strong>ABOVE ALL, I TRUST YOU CAN DO WELL! GOOD LUCK!<\/strong><\/p><br><br><br><p><strong>ADDITIONAL INFORMATION:<\/strong>&nbsp;Moreover, prior to your FINAL JOB INTERVIEW, we will have your&nbsp;<strong>MOCK JOB INTERVIEW<\/strong>&nbsp;which will start on Monday (OCTOBER 2, 2023) -&nbsp;<em>new schedule<\/em>.<\/p><br><p>We have 2 batches for the Mock Job Interview:<\/p><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>DAY 1 (OCTOBER 2; ROOM 411) - DREAMYBULLS, CEA, &amp; FANTASTIC 4<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>DAY 2 (OCTOBER 4; ROOM 406) - JR-N, GROUPCHAT, &amp; ORCAS<\/strong><\/span><\/p><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>TIME: 2:30 - 3:45 PM<\/strong><\/span><\/p><br><br><p>NOTE 1:&nbsp;<strong>Just come to class IF IT'S YOUR SCHEDULE.<\/strong><\/p><p>NOTE 2:&nbsp;<strong>ONLINE STUDENTS OR THOSE WHO DON'T HAVE GROUPS MAY CHOOSE ONE FROM THE ABOVE DATES.&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p><br><p>WHAT TO BRING:&nbsp;<strong>Printed Cover Letter; Skills-based CV; and RUBRIC<\/strong><\/p><br><p>WHAT TO WEAR:&nbsp;<strong>Casual&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p><p>(You may also wear formal attire to at least practice with how you handle the attire.)<\/p><br><br><p>PURPOSE:&nbsp;<strong>FOR PRACTICE AND FEEDBACK<\/strong>. Also, if ever you get low score in the Final Interview but a high score in the mock interview, I can dispute your final grade.<\/p><br><br><p><strong>REMINDER: THIS IS PART OF YOUR FORMATIVE ASSESSMENT. HOWEVER,&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p><p><strong>I STILL EXPECT THAT YOU DO WELL IN PREPARATION FOR THE FINAL ASSESSMENT.<\/strong><\/p><br><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>FOR FULLY ONLINE STUDENTS: YOU HAVE A CHOICE WHETHER YOU JOIN THE MOCK INTERVIEW (16 Points in your Formative Assessment). HOWEVER, THE FINAL INTERVIEW ON SATURDAY (OCT 7, 2023) MUST BE ATTENDED - AS WE DON'T HAVE ONLINE SCHEDULES FOR THE JOB INTERVIEW. I HOPE YOU CAN FIND TIME.<\/strong><\/span><\/p><br><br><p>Thank you. Good luck!<\/p><br><br><br>",
