		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<!-- {\"bbMLEditorVersion\":1} --><div>\n <p>Hello, everyone. Please review the details below for your Module 1 Final Assessment next week.<\/p>\n \n <p><span style=\"color: #E72218\"><strong>FINAL ASSESSMENTS\/EXAMS ARE F2F.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n <p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>NO HARD COPY OF THE RUBRIC, NO EXAM.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n <br>\n <p><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.cslocation@X@Individual%20Assessment%20Rubric.pdf\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;Individual Assessment Rubric.pdf&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Individual Assessment Rubric.pdf&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;Individual Assessment Rubric.pdf&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:113749,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;application\/pdf&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;attachment&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/malayanmindanao.blackboard.com\/sessions\/D1\/D1607EC457B3411CA21E6CE2E905CF80\/c1315de00be04b7f917fe24191c5f2f0\/Individual%20Assessment%20Rubric.pdf&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;Individual Assessment Rubric.pdf&quot;}\">Individual Assessment Rubric.pdf<\/a><\/p>\n <br>\n <p>THE FINAL ASSESSMENT IS INTENDED FOR 2 DAYS.<\/p>\n <p>(Depending on the number of students, it is possible to complete it on the first day.)<\/p>\n \n <p>ASSESSMENT:&nbsp;<strong>INDIVIDUAL ORAL PRESENTATION<\/strong>&nbsp;(Impromptu Speaking)<\/p>\n <p>ASSESSMENT COVERAGE:&nbsp;<strong>ALL MODULE 1 CONTENTS<\/strong><\/p>\n <br>\n <p><span style=\"color: #E72218\">Day\/Time\/Room: Remains the same if there are no memos to change.<\/span><\/p>\n \n <p>Instructions:<\/p>\n <p>1. Each student will be asked 3 out of the 25 questions.<\/p>\n <p>2. Each question is to be answered in 30-45 seconds.<\/p>\n <p>3.&nbsp;<strong>EACH STUDENT MUST PRINT A COPY OF THE RUBRIC.<\/strong><\/p>\n <p>4. The questions shall be randomly chosen.<\/p>\n <p>5. The rubric is presented for grading:<\/p>\n <br>\n \n <p><span style=\"color: #E72218\">NO NEED FOR A BOOKLET. HOWEVER, THE STUDENTS MUST PRINT THE RUBRIC FOR THEIR GRADES.<\/span><\/p>\n <p><span style=\"color: #E72218\">NO HARD COPY OF THE RUBRIC, NO EXAM.<\/span><\/p>\n \n <p><strong>Sample questions:<\/strong><\/p>\n <p>1. Why is effective communication important in our society?<\/p>\n <p>2. Explain the disparity between formal and informal communication?<\/p>\n <p>3. What are the forms\/modes of communication? Explain.<\/p>\n \n \n <p>Reminders: Double check your Module 1 contents. For F2F activities (main activities only) that you missed, always check Mdoule 1 \"Submission Bin for Online Students \/ Daily Log\" under Course Content for the instructions on how and what to submit. If you haven't joined a&nbsp;<strong>group reporting<\/strong>, there's also the instruction there. You may watch the recorded classes as well. All online students must submit outputs from the same activities. All submissions will close on&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #E72218\">September 5 at 11:59 PM.<\/span><\/p>\n \n <p>See you tomorrow.&nbsp;<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Thank you, and good luck!<\/p>\n <br>\n <br>\n<\/div>",
