		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_03831c52-f339-4523-a1bd-db69acbcca9c\"><br><p><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17791295_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;Slide1.JPG&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Slide1.JPG&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;Slide1.JPG.jpg&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:174501,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/jpeg&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inline&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/5D\/5D7F7A580F61AADE8328707FC533A8B9\/e28449aeaef64e898344e93cfcaec931\/Slide1.JPG&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;Slide1.JPG&quot;}\">Slide1.JPG<\/a><\/p><p><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17791296_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;Slide2.JPG&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Slide2.JPG&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;Slide2.JPG.jpg&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:147776,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/jpeg&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inline&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/5D\/5D7F7A580F61AADE8328707FC533A8B9\/3385880fea7f4736812c4c363f23bf04\/Slide2.JPG&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;Slide2.JPG&quot;}\">Slide2.JPG<\/a><\/p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">For every FTF session, there will be activities. The FTF activities will be part of the&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\"><strong>20 points Class Participation per module.&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">You are highly encouraged to join the FTF sessions so you may experience collaboration with your classmates physically.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">If you are geographically incapable, you will be given same tasks as those who would do them FTF, but you will have to submit them online.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p><br><\/div><div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_e48da272-d1fd-446e-a008-606e38408718\"><p>As you navigate this course, please be guided of the following:<\/p><p><strong>FORMATIVE ASSESSMENTS&nbsp;<\/strong><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong>(30% percent of the module grade)<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>&nbsp;a. Module 1 Quizzes Due Date:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>&nbsp;b. Module 2 Quizzes Due Date:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>&nbsp;c. Module 3 Quizzes Due Date:<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><p><strong>6.Each module has a SUMMATIVE assessment<\/strong>&nbsp;that will be recorded.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong>(70% percent of the module grade)<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\">a. Module 1 Final Assessment:&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>Due Date:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\">b. Module 2 Final Assessment:<\/span><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>&nbsp;Due Date:&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\">c. Module 3 Final Assessment:&nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>Due Date:<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p><strong>7.If you have questions and clarifications, message me through Outlook or Teams during sociable hours. (Monday to Friday, 8:00 am to 4:00 pm)<\/strong><\/p><p><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\"><strong>8.<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 0.875rem;\">As you email, introduce yourself, mention the course and section, and politely state your concern. Observe proper email etiquette.<\/span><\/p><p><strong>Modular System<\/strong><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>Module Grade of INC (Incomplete)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p>‚Ä¢ A student who was not able to submit a course requirement due to medical or emergency reasons will get an incomplete grade of INC.&nbsp;<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ Incomplete grade of INC can be completed to any passing mark, from 3.00 to 1.00.<\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>Module Grade of IP (In Progress)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p>‚Ä¢ A student who failed a module will get a module grade of IP.&nbsp;<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ An IP module grade can only be converted, upon completion, to a grade of 3.00.&nbsp;<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ If a student passes at least one module,<\/p><p>o He\/she will just need to convert all modules with IP to 3.00, and not to repeat the whole course.&nbsp;<\/p><p>o He\/she will be given an additional term to convert all modules with a grade of IP to 3.00 for free.&nbsp;<\/p><p>o A course with an I or IP in any of the modules by the end of the term will get a course grade of IP for the course.&nbsp;<\/p><p>o A course will remain to have a course grade of IP until the student gets a passing grade in all modules.<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ After an additional term, if the student is not able to convert the IP to 3.00, the student needs to re-enroll the module as a Remedial Module in the following term, if offered, and not the whole course.&nbsp;<\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>What will be the basis of a Grade of 5.00 (F)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p>‚Ä¢ The student will get a course grade of 5.00&nbsp;<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ in case he\/she violated the Academic Integrity Policy of the School in any of the modules (a module grade of 5.00 will be given) regardless of class standing.&nbsp;<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ in case he incurred a 100% absence (module grade of ABS) in any of the modules, regardless of his performance in other modules.<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ if he gets IP in all the modules. Under this situation, the student needs to re-enroll the course in the following term, if offered.&nbsp;<\/p><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><strong>Converting Modules that you Fail into Passing Mark<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p>‚Ä¢ If you fail Module 1, you get IP, not 5.00&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ If you fail Module 2, you get IP, not 5.00<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ If you fail Module 3, you get IP, not 5.00<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ If you get IP to all modules, you get a course grade of 5.00. That means You need to re-enroll the course.<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ If you pass at least one module in a course, you will be given an additional term to convert IP grade into 3.00. You repeat the module not the course.&nbsp;<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ If you fail to complete all the modules after one term, you will need to re-enroll modules as remedial modules.<\/p><p>‚Ä¢ You need to pass all modules in a prerequisite course before you can enroll the advanced course.&nbsp;<\/p><p>Please read the file for the Modular and OBE Grading System.<\/p><p><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17791297_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;Orientation Guide for Modular and OBE Grading System Ver.1.pdf&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Orientation Guide for Modular and OBE Grading System Ver.1.pdf&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;Orientation Guide for Modular and OBE Grading System Ver.1.pdf&quot;,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;application\/pdf&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inline&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/8D\/8DE1727CBCCDF74E0FE4ABF676192EF7\/c0660bbaec154861bd98bf3bd8e798d7\/Orientation%20Guide%20for%20Modular%20and%20OBE%20Grading%20System%20Ver.1.pdf&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;Orientation Guide for Modular and OBE Grading System Ver.1.pdf&quot;}\">Orientation Guide for Modular and OBE Grading System Ver.1.pdf<\/a><\/p><\/div>",
