		"ITEM_ID" : 359135490,
		"ITEM_NAME" : "ultraDocumentBody",
		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17831086_1\" data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_688d6cbe-22fd-4031-a0a8-998d4fa7587b\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;isDecorative&quot;:true,&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;MEC101-2.jpg&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;MEC101-2.jpg&quot;,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/jpeg&quot;}\">MEC101-2.jpg<\/a><div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_76be5d41-7cb2-4607-ab6c-00476547c91c\"><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>Course Overview<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><ul><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Course Code:<\/strong>&nbsp;MEC101-2<\/li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Course Title:<\/strong>&nbsp;STATICS OF RIGID BODIES<\/li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Pre-requisite:<\/strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: black\">Phys031 and Math052<\/span><\/li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Co-requisite:<\/strong>&nbsp;None<\/li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Credit Units(s):&nbsp;<\/strong>Three (3) units Lecture<\/li><\/ul><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>Course Description<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: black\">Statics of rigid bodies is concerned with the behavior of bodies at rest under the action of forces, moments and couples. The concept of these forces, moments and couple, and their systems is firstly delivered leading to analysis of the principles of resultants and equilibrium which enables engineering solutions to statically determinate bodies or systems.<\/span><\/p><br><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>Course Outcomes<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><p>In this course, you will:<\/p><ol><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Demonstrate the application of force and moment vectors, and resultants to analyze static equilibrium of bodies.<\/li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Solve problems regarding analysis of structures such as trusses, beams and cables in a planar system and problems involving effect of dry friction on objects.<\/li><li style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Determine the centroid and moment of inertia of member cross sections.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_85b95ab6-134c-4e7a-b55f-5c70e93296f8\"><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>Course Schedule<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong>Monday, Wednesday, and Friday | 6:15 PM to 7:30 PM | Room 514<\/strong><\/span><\/p><p>Note that schedules can be requested to be on FLUX mode (simultaneous Face-to-face and online) upon request of the class. All Friday and Saturday classes will be delivered online, either bichronously or asynchronously.<\/p><\/div><div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_bbf2a06c-e3ca-4c47-b83c-99b4c45e9fbd\"><br><p><span style=\"color: #e72218\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>Course Files<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p><br><p><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17965524_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;MEC101-2_Syllabus.23.24.pdf&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;MEC101-2_Syllabus.23.24.pdf&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;MEC101-2_Syllabus.23.24.pdf&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:686811,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;application\/pdf&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inline&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/C4\/C4AF4BE8A22C7B777A060CCA123FCA11\/fe2789967e28457f869107ed3b858ab6\/MEC101-2_Syllabus.23.24.pdf&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;MEC101-2_Syllabus.23.24.pdf&quot;}\">MEC101-2_Syllabus.23.24.pdf<\/a><\/p><br><\/div>",
