		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_d6d3eb39-54a1-44ab-b1ef-4992cc2faea8\"><h4>1. Eye Level<\/h4><h6>&nbsp;<\/h6><p><span style=\"color: #000000\">This has the camera angle at the same level as the subject's eyes. It provides a neutral and natural perspective, making the audience feel like they are on the same level as the characters, fostering a sense of connection and empathy.<\/span><\/p><p><img src=\"https:\/\/static.wixstatic.com\/media\/cb1974_76fd155d0973451285ab6d90c0e2f795~mv2.jpg\/v1\/fill\/w_740,h_493,al_c,q_85,usm_0.66_1.00_0.01,enc_auto\/cb1974_76fd155d0973451285ab6d90c0e2f795~mv2.jpg\"><\/p><pre>&nbsp;<\/pre><br><h4><strong>2. Low Angle<\/strong><\/h4><h6><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h6><p>The camera is placed below the subject, looking up. It makes the subject appear larger and more powerful, often used to convey authority, dominance, or intimidation.<\/p><h6><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-18620419_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;image 1 (1).png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;image 1 (1).png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;image 1 (1).png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:548519,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/63\/63EBAF93DD276B99C65508619C1084FA\/bec4962545dd4c65ade3a892c824eab8\/image%201%20%281%29.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;image 1 (1).png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:781,&quot;height&quot;:520.3148648648648}\">image 1 (1).png<\/a><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h6><pre>&nbsp;<\/pre><h6><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h6><h4><strong>3. Worm's Eye View<\/strong><\/h4><h6><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h6><p><span style=\"color: #000000\">Similar to a low angle but taken from an even lower perspective, almost at ground level. It can make subjects seem intimidating and imposing, often used to create tension or showcase a character's point of view in action scenes.<\/span><\/p><h6><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-18620422_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;image 3.png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;image 3.png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;image 3.png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:318845,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/63\/63EBAF93DD276B99C65508619C1084FA\/21b4daa1f63747a482da8a71c0e65fe4\/image%203.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;image 3.png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:779,&quot;height&quot;:518.9824324324325}\">image 3.png<\/a><\/h6><pre>&nbsp;<\/pre><br><h4><strong>4.&nbsp;<\/strong><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>High Angle<\/strong><\/span><\/h4><br><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"color: #000000\">The camera is positioned above the subject, looking down. It often makes the subject appear smaller and less powerful, emphasizing vulnerability or submission.<\/span><\/p><h6><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-18620423_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;image 3 (1).png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (1).png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (1).png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:764386,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/63\/63EBAF93DD276B99C65508619C1084FA\/a08dd9874926455894d918ff49f1abc5\/image%203%20%281%29.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (1).png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:796,&quot;height&quot;:556.6354609929078}\">image 3 (1).png<\/a><\/h6><pre>&nbsp;<\/pre><br><h4><strong>5.&nbsp;<\/strong><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Bird's Eye View<\/strong><\/span><\/h4><h6>&nbsp;<\/h6><p style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"color: #000000\">The camera is positioned above the subject, looking down. It often makes the subject appear smaller and less powerful, emphasizing vulnerability or submission.<\/span><\/p><h6><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-18620424_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;image 3 (2).png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (2).png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (2).png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:693651,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/63\/63EBAF93DD276B99C65508619C1084FA\/fe5f8bd7c2934a3d947daaced7cb1686\/image%203%20%282%29.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (2).png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:796,&quot;height&quot;:530.3081081081081}\">image 3 (2).png<\/a><\/h6><pre>&nbsp;<\/pre><br><h4><strong>6. Dutch Angle<\/strong><\/h4><h6>&nbsp;<\/h6><p><span style=\"color: #000000\">The camera is tilted to create a diagonal horizon. It's used to create a sense of unease, disorientation, or tension, often employed in suspenseful or chaotic scenes.<\/span><\/p><h6><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-18620425_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;image 3 (3).png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (3).png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (3).png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:243856,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/63\/63EBAF93DD276B99C65508619C1084FA\/0bff197b2f5048da8d12bb242c4d98c7\/image%203%20%283%29.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (3).png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:796,&quot;height&quot;:530.3081081081081}\">image 3 (3).png<\/a><\/h6><pre>&nbsp;<\/pre><br><h4><strong>7.&nbsp;<\/strong><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Close-up Angle<\/strong><\/span><\/h4><h6>&nbsp;<\/h6><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"color: #000000\">This shot frames a subject's face or a specific detail, emphasizing emotion, reactions, or important objects. It's used to convey intimacy, intensity, or to focus the audience's attention on critical elements.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-18620426_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;image 3 (4).png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (4).png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (4).png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:522128,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/63\/63EBAF93DD276B99C65508619C1084FA\/dd64329d720c4e48831d7810ccdea031\/image%203%20%284%29.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;image 3 (4).png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:796,&quot;height&quot;:530.3081081081081}\">image 3 (4).png<\/a><\/p><br><pre>&nbsp;<\/pre><br><h4><strong>8.&nbsp;<\/strong><span style=\"color: #000000\"><strong>Wide Angle<\/strong><\/span><\/h4><h6>&nbsp;<\/h6><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><span style=\"color: #000000\">A wide-angle lens captures a broader view of the scene, often used to establish the setting, show the environment, or emphasize the vastness of a location. It can also create a sense of distortion and depth, depending on the focal length.<\/span><\/p><p><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-18620427_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;image 4.png&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;image 4.png&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;image 4.png&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:541435,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/png&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/63\/63EBAF93DD276B99C65508619C1084FA\/88d724cda64642c99db11449fb4162c2\/image%204.png&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;image 4.png&quot;,&quot;width&quot;:796,&quot;height&quot;:530.3081081081081}\">image 4.png<\/a><\/p><\/div>",
