		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<!-- {\"bbMLEditorVersion\":1} --><div>\n <p>Dear Students,<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>I'm reminding everyone to please answer the&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">Module 1 Formative Assessments<\/span><\/strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">get a score of at least 60%<\/span><\/strong>&nbsp;so that you can access the next content. You can also view your progress in the progress bar seen under Module 1.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Here are additional reminders:<\/p>\n <br>\n <p><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong>1)<\/strong><\/span>&nbsp;If you get to formative assessment 1.3 (FA - 1.3), please network and find groupmates from your classmates. If you can't really find any, please contact me via our Official MS Teams Group so that I may assist you. I'm not grouping you myself since networking is a really useful skill that you need to learn as well.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p><span style=\"color: #1c8845\"><strong>2)<\/strong><\/span>&nbsp;The Summative Assessment for Module 1 will be on the 5th week so please answer your formative assessments to make the content you will need for the summative assessment available for you to study.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p><span style=\"color: #a234b5\"><strong>3)<\/strong><\/span>&nbsp;Unfortunately, late enrollees will have to catch-up with the course since you are well aware that you enrolled late and it's no longer our responsibility to go back to the topics that were already discussed. There are recordings for the synchronous classless for you to view for that.&nbsp;<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Again, since Mathematics in the Modern World is a fully-online, Bichronous Course, you are responsible for your own progress in the times that we don't meet synchronously. Please be responsible and deliver what is expected of you as students.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Thanks and if there are any questions,&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">please ask me using our Official MS Teams Group<\/span><\/strong>.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Details concerning the Summative Assessment schedules will be announced on a later time.<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>Cheers,<\/p>\n <p>Sir Earvin<\/p>\n<\/div>",
