		"ITEM_NAME" : "WELCOME TO HUM018-1 WORLD LITERATURE!  ",
		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<!-- {\"bbMLEditorVersion\":1} --><div>\n <p>Hello, class. I just finished my onboarding yesterday. I am still trying to catch up with everything. Rest assured; we will be at full speed by next week.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <p><strong>Congratulations on enrolling in HUM18-1, World Literature.&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n <br>\n <p>This course is a study of the literary masterpieces of the world. It aims to expose students to different readings from different countries and continents around the globe, from the early ages to the contemporary and 21st-century literature. This will help enrich their perception of the varied continental stories, cultures, and lives, contributing to life-long learning by understanding how similar yet distinct literary art can be from lands across the globe.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <p>HUM18-1 is simply structured. It is composed of three modules: Ancient Mesopotamia, Greek and African masterpieces; Asian masterpieces; and European and American masterpieces.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <p>Before proceeding, you have to do three things.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <p>First, you have to introduce yourself to everyone else in our discussion forum:&nbsp;<strong>Self-Introductions<\/strong>. Please tell us a little bit about yourself, your program and why you chose it, your location, and other things you might want to share with the class. You may interact with your classmates by commenting on their introduction posts.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <p>Second, you must add yourselves to your respective class teams. This will allow us to interact as a class easier. Please make sure you joined the correct Teams. You have to do this as soon as possible.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <table>\n  <tbody>\n   <tr>\n    <td><p><strong>Class Code&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n    <td><p><strong>Teams Link\/Code&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n   <\/tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td><p>A201&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n    <td><p>5bqf3u3&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n   <\/tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td><p>A202&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n    <td><p>0wh4k6g&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n   <\/tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td><p>A203&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n    <td><p>b2bauar&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n   <\/tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td><p>A204&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n    <td><p>zmr6lzk&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n   <\/tr>\n   <tr>\n    <td><p>A205&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n    <td><p>8cg3uzb&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p><\/td>\n   <\/tr>\n  <\/tbody>\n <\/table>\n <br>\n <p>Third, you must also add yourself to a general Teams I created for all the students I am handling this semester.&nbsp;<strong>The code is 0xaormw.&nbsp;<\/strong>You must make sure you add yourself to this team so you will be updated on when we will have an online class.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <p>For this semester, our classes will be online. We can meet on Saturday, August 12 (specific time to follow ‚Äì the update will be posted on our general teams), just for a quick orientation on the course and setting expectations. We will also discuss how we will do our sessions for this semester.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n \n <p>I am looking forward to meeting all of you! See you soon (virtually)!&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>",
