		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17837727_1\" data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_a98cb6d2-fd3f-4370-8532-b2206b598eef\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;cover.gif&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;cover.gif&quot;,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/gif&quot;}\">cover.gif<\/a> \n<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_c581bb75-9298-449d-b77f-13f800feff53\"> \n <p><span style=\"color: #000000\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>Course Description<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: black\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">This course is a study of the literary masterpieces of the world. It aims to expose students to different readings from different countries and continents around the globe, from the early ages to the contemporary and 21st century literature. This will help enrich their perception of the varied continental stories, cultures and lives, contributing to life-long learning by understanding how similar yet distinct literary art can be from lands across the globe.<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p> \n<\/div> \n<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_1567decd-eacd-40f4-90a6-b0e193df6d16\"> \n <br> \n <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav\/xid-17837728_1\" data-bbtype=\"attachment\" data-bbfile=\"{&quot;alternativeText&quot;:&quot;Course Outcomes_HUM018-1.jpg&quot;,&quot;displayName&quot;:&quot;Course Outcomes_HUM018-1.jpg&quot;,&quot;fileName&quot;:&quot;Course Outcomes_HUM018-1.jpg&quot;,&quot;fileSize&quot;:89571,&quot;isDecorative&quot;:true,&quot;mimeType&quot;:&quot;image\/jpeg&quot;,&quot;render&quot;:&quot;inlineOnly&quot;,&quot;resourceUrl&quot;:&quot;@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@sessions\/59\/590231C3992502FCE6F70892615D6B83\/b65239f321644eb6acd0d9a1cfd83275\/Course%20Outcomes_HUM018-1.jpg&quot;,&quot;linkName&quot;:&quot;Course Outcomes_HUM018-1.jpg&quot;}\">Course Outcomes_HUM018-1.jpg<\/a><\/p> \n <br> \n<\/div> \n<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_dabd9b7d-1e9a-4efd-8ead-53fa2e221437\"> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>Course References<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Abrams (2015). A glossary of literary terms 11e. Cengage<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Arana, R.K. et al (2019). Integrated English for effective communication: Philippine Literature. The Phoenix Publishing House, Inc.: Quezon City, Philippines.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Bolt, Carol (2018). The literary book of answers: Let great books guide the way. Hachette Books: New York, USA.<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Lacia, F. C. et al (2015). The literatures of the Philippines 3rd Edition. REX Bookstore: Manila, Philippines.&nbsp;<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Lapid, M. G. et al (2018). English communication arts and skills through Anglo-American and Philippine literature 8th edition. The Phoenix Publishing House, Inc.: Quezon City, Philippines.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Lapid, M. G. et al (2018). English communication arts and skills through Philippine literature 8th edition. The Phoenix Publishing House, Inc.: Quezon City, Philippines.&nbsp;<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Lazzari (2020). Exploring art: A global thematic approach 5e revised. Cengage<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Martin, M. G. P. et al (2016). English communication arts and skills beyond borders: reading literature in the 21st century. The Phoenix Publishing House, Inc.: Quezon City, Philippines.<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n <p><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.125rem;\">Purdue University (n. d). Literary Theory and Schools of Criticism.&nbsp;Accessed in June 2021 from&nbsp;https:\/\/owl.purdue.edu\/owl\/subject_specific_writing\/writing_in_literature\/literary_theory_and_schools_of_criticism\/index.html&nbsp;<\/span><\/span><\/p> \n<\/div>",
