		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<div data-bbid=\"bbml-editor-id_abce1a91-7b0b-4d81-be4c-3918ad154690\"><h4 style=\"text-align: left;\"><img src=\"https:\/\/cdn.dribbble.com\/users\/228367\/screenshots\/4603754\/chemistryset_dribbble.gif\" alt=\"Chemistry Set. by Dan Stack on Dribbble\"><\/h4><h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #1c8845\"><span style=\"font-family: Courier New;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>WELCOME TO&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/h4><h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #1c8845\"><span style=\"font-family: Courier New;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5rem;\"><strong>CHM031-CHEMISTRY FOR ENGINEERS LECTURE COURSE!<\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/h4><br><p><span style=\"color: #666666\">All lecture classes are in<\/span><span style=\"color: #666666\"><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">Blended-All mode<\/span><\/strong><\/span><span style=\"color: #666666\">. Meaning, we will have&nbsp;<\/span><strong>Face-to-Face, Synchronous Online, and Asynchronous Online&nbsp;<\/strong><span style=\"color: #666666\"><strong>sessions<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"color: #666666\">.<\/span><\/p><p><span style=\"color: #666666\">Below is our lecture class schedule for this course and section (mode of learning may be subject to change per week, please keep updated with announcements):<\/span><\/p><ul><li><span style=\"color: #e72218\">Mondays (10:45 AM - 12:00 PM) - FLUX (R411)<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #e72218\">Wednesdays (10:45 AM - 12:00 PM) - FLUX (R411)<\/span><\/li><li><span style=\"color: #e72218\">Fridays (10:45 AM - 12:00 PM) - Digital Day\/ FLUX (R411)<\/span><\/li><\/ul><p><span style=\"color: #2d3b45\">Please review all of the following information in this BB Ultra:<\/span><\/p><ul><li><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong>Announcements<\/strong><\/span>&nbsp;-&nbsp;As it says, Course Announcements. Please check it regularly.<\/li><li><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong>Course Introduction Module<\/strong><\/span>- All the essential information and guidelines for this course, course instructor, syllabus, references, MMCM History, and more<\/li><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">Course Instructor<\/span><\/em><\/strong>&nbsp;- Information about your instructor<\/li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">Syllabus<\/span><\/em><\/strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/em><em>-<\/em>&nbsp;Formal description of the course, policies, and course schedule<\/li><li><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">References<\/span><\/em><\/strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Standard resources for online students<\/li><\/ul><li><span style=\"color: #046ef6\"><strong>Modules<\/strong><\/span>&nbsp;-&nbsp;Weekly learning materials and may contain the following:<\/li><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">01_Lecture Notes<\/span><\/em><\/strong>&nbsp;- for the weekly lesson<\/li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">02_Book Readings<\/span><\/em><\/strong>&nbsp;- for additional reference<\/li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">03_Lecture Recording<\/span><\/em><\/strong>&nbsp;- FLUX recording<\/li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">04_Lecture Slides<\/span><\/em><\/strong>&nbsp;- for the weekly lesson<\/li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">05_Quiz\/Practice Tests<\/span><\/em><\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/ul><p>When you are ready,&nbsp;please go to&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #a234b5\"><strong>Module 0<\/strong><\/span>. There you will:<\/p><p>1. Be asked to&nbsp;<strong>introduce yourself<\/strong>&nbsp;on the Discussion Board to the class (you will earn 10 points for completing this).<\/p><p>2. After that, you may navigate through the course.&nbsp;Each week of the course has its own comprehensive set of resources within the Modules. I will only open the weekly folders per week to avoid information overload on your part.<\/p><p><strong>See you at our Course Orientation!<\/strong><\/p><h6><span style=\"color: #a234b5\"><em>Good luck and have fun learning Chemistry!&nbsp;<\/em><\/span><\/h6><h6><span style=\"color: #a234b5\"><em>- Ma'am Lorraine :)<\/em><\/span><\/h6><\/div>",
