		"ITEM_NAME" : "CREATE A THREAD",
		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<p>The phrase \"It takes a thousand of times to develop a thing but it only takes a fraction of a section to destroy the same\" reminds me of trust. It may be a small word but it holds a lot meaning and significance. It takes time to be developed. Trusting someone or something is not easy, especially in our world today wherein danger is unexpected. You will have to work for it in order for you to gain trust. However, if you break it, it is very hard to get the trust back, sometimes you can never get it back. I can relate the story of \"The boy who cried wolf\" wherein he fooled a lot of people but when the time comes that his story came out to be true, now the villagers won't believe him because he already broke their trust. I am a firm believer that trust is a blessing to all of us, it is part of the bond and love for each and every one of us. That is why we should develop it and not destroy it so that we won't suffer the consequences.<\/p>",
