		"ITEM_NAME" : "Forum Javellana",
		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<p>In my understanding, the maxim above explains that even if something is developed with utmost effort and dedication it could all be in vain with one single mistake. An example that I can associate this with would be something like a friendship you have with a person. No matter how close you are with this person, if you make a single mistake that would cause that person to lose trust in you the friendship that you've cultivated with them might be strained or completely ruined.<\/p>",
