		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<p style=\"text-align: justify;margin: 0.0in 0.0in 8.0pt;line-height: 107.0%;font-size: 11.0pt;font-family: Calibri , sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style=\"font-family: Arial , sans-serif;\">Happiness gained from people‚Äôs agony is nothing more than worldly attainment. Happiness should never be rooted from another individual‚Äôs suffering, for it should not come with such a profane cost. The true essence of happiness is achieved when one wholeheartedly contributes to another person‚Äôs needs. Happiness through kind acts such as charity is much more significant, bearing in mind that it should be just, and should only be attributed for the common good of people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>",
