		"COURSE_ID" : 3512986,
		"COURSE_NAME" : "Logic and Critical Thinking",
		"ITEM_ID" : 362318840,
		"ITEM_NAME" : "Kumain ka na ba?",
		"ITEM_DESCRIPTION" : "<p>I can co-relate this with trust since it may take years to gain and give someone your trust and it can just be destroyed with one action. Regaining it is no longer our control and it is just sad knowing you destroyed something that cant be returned. Other than trust, it could also be discipline since it requires time for us to be disciplined in what we practice. Just like when we workout, we try our best to eat clean but when we break our rule and it becomes a habit then we will go back to square one&nbsp;<\/p>",
